text: Henry Z. Osborne Henry Zenas Osborne (October 4, 1848 - February 8, 1923) was an American Republican politician. ==Biography== He was born in New Lebanon, New York on October 4, 1848. In 1873 he worked for the New York Times. He was elected to the United States House of Representatives from California and served from March 4, 1917, until his death. Osborne died at age 74 in Los Angeles, California. He is interred in Angelus-Rosedale Cemetery. ==See also== *List of United States Congress members who died in office (1900–49) ==References== ==Further reading== Category:Members of the United States House of Representatives from California Category:1848 births Category:1923 deaths Category:Burials at Angelus-Rosedale Cemetery Category:People from New Lebanon, New York Category:California Republicans Category:Republican Party members of the United States House of Representatives
